data.chText: 区分；辨别；分清
data.enText: to recognize the difference between two people or things

data.chText: 儿童到什么年龄才能明辨是非？
data.enText: At what age are children able to distinguish between right and wrong?

data.chText: 很难分辨出一对孪生儿谁是谁。
data.enText: It was hard to distinguish one twin from the other.

data.chText: 有时候现实和幻想很难区分。
data.enText: Sometimes reality and fantasy are hard to distinguish.

before.enText: not used in the progressive tenses

data.chText: 成为…的特征；使具有…的特色；使有别于
data.enText: to be a characteristic that makes two people, animals or things different

data.chText: 是什么使得她有别于班上其他同学呢？
data.enText: What was it that distinguished her from her classmates?

data.chText: 雄鸟喙呈红色，有别于雌鸟。
data.enText: The male bird is distinguished from the female by its red beak.

data.chText: 你的猫有什么特殊标记吗？
data.enText: Does your cat have any distinguishing marks?

data.chText: 看清；认出；听出

before.enText: not used in the progressive tenses

data.enText: to be able to see or hear sth

data.chText: 我听不清她说的话，但听得出她很紧张不安。
data.enText: I could not distinguish her words, but she sounded agitated.

data.chText: 使出众；使著名；使受人青睐
data.enText: to do sth so well that people notice and admire you

data.chText: 作为运动员她已享有盛名。
data.enText: She has already distinguished herself as an athlete.

data.chText: 这种鸟很容易辨认雌雄。
data.enText: The male bird is easily distinguishable from the female.

data.chText: 在雾中很难看清海岸。
data.enText: The coast was barely distinguishable in the mist.

data.text: identify ♦ recognize ♦ make out ♦ discern ♦ pick out ♦ distinguish

data.chText: 以上各词均含认出、辨别出之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to be able to see or hear sb/sth and especially to be able to say who or what they are.
identify

data.chText: 指确认、认出、鉴定：
data.enText: to be able to say who or what sb/sth is

data.chText: 她认出了袭击她的人。
data.enText: She was able to identify her attacker.
recognize

data.chText: 指认识、认出、辨别出：
data.enText: to know who sb is or what sth is when you see or hear them/it, because you have seen or heard them/it before

data.chText: 他一进屋我就认出了他。
data.enText: I recognized him as soon as he came in the room.
make sb/sth out

data.chText: 指看清、听清、分清、辨认清楚：
data.enText: to manage to see or hear sb/sth that is not very clear

data.chText: 黑暗中我只看出了一个人的轮廓。
data.enText: I could just make out a figure in the darkness.
discern

data.chText: 指觉察出、识别、依稀看出、分辨出、听出：
data.enText: ( formal ) to recognize or know sth, especially sth that is not obvious; to manage to see or hear sb/sth that is not very clear

data.chText: 了解公众支持的广泛程度常常是困难的。
data.enText: It is often difficult to discern how widespread public support is.
pick sb/sth out

data.chText: 指从…中认出来、辨别出：
data.enText: to recognize sb/sth from among other people or things

data.chText: 看你能不能把我从这张照片上认出来。
data.enText: See if you can pick me out in this photo.
distinguish

data.chText: （通常用于否定句）指看清、认出、听出：
data.enText: (usually used in negative statements) ( rather formal ) to manage to see or hear sb/sth that is not very clear

data.chText: 她在渐暗的暮色中看不清楚汽车的型号。
data.enText: She could not distinguish the make of the car in the fading light.

data.chText: 用make sb/sth out还是distinguish？
distinguish较make sb/sth out正式，多以名词短语作宾语，make sb/sth out多以what或who引出的从句作宾语：
data.enText: Distinguish is more formal than make sb/sth out and is more likely to have a noun phrase as object. Make sb/sth out is more likely to have a clause with what or who as object.

data.chText: 我听不清她说的话。
data.enText: I could not distinguish her words.

data.chText: 我听不清她在说什么。
data.enText: I couldn't make out what she was saying.
make sb/sth out or distinguish?
to identify/recognize sb/sth as sb/sth
to identify/recognize/make out/discern/distinguish who/what/how…
to easily/barely/just identify/recognize/make out/discern/pick out/distinguish sb/sth
can/could identify/recognize/make out/discern/pick out/distinguish sb/sth
a way/means of identifying/recognizing/discerning/distinguishing sb/sth

simple_means.memory_skill: di〔s〕分离 + stingu 刺；刺激 + ish 使… → 把不同的刺分离 → 区别

example: We distinguish several kinds of maple

tr: be a distinctive feature, attribute, or trait
sometimes in a very positive sense
example: His modesty distinguishes him from his peers

tr: identify as in botany or biology, for example

example: The fleeing convicts were picked out of the darkness by the watchful prison guards
I can't make out the faces in this photograph

value.def: If you can distinguish one thing from another or distinguish between two things, you can see or understand how they are different.

example.ex: Could he distinguish right from wrong?...
Research suggests that babies learn to see by distinguishing between areas of light and dark...
example.tran: 研究表明婴儿通过辨别光亮和黑暗的区域来学会看东西。

example.ex: It is necessary to distinguish the policies of two successive governments.
example.tran: 分清前后两届政府的政策很有必要。

value.def: A feature or quality that distinguishes one thing from another causes the two things to be regarded as different, because only the first thing has the feature or quality.

example.ex: There is something about music that distinguishes it from all other art forms...
example.tran: 音乐的某种特质使其有别于所有其他艺术形式。

example.ex: The bird has no distinguishing features.
example.tran: 这只鸟没有明显的特征。

value.def: If you can distinguish something, you can see, hear, or taste it although it is very difficult to detect.

example.ex: There were cries, calls. He could distinguish voices.
example.tran: 有哭声、喊声——他能听出不同的声音。

value.def: If you distinguish yourself, you do something that makes you famous or important.

example.ex: Over the next few years he distinguished himself as a leading constitutional scholar...
example.tran: 在接下来的几年里，他作为一名宪法研究领域最杰出的学者而声名远扬。

example.ex: They distinguished themselves at the Battle of Assaye.
example.tran: 他们在阿瑟耶之战中一战成名。

partsOfSpeech.dec: dis 分开 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 → 把刺分开后显得清楚的；明显的 → 清楚的；明显的
dis 分开 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 + ion，distinct 的名词 → 区别；优秀
dis 分开 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 + ive …的 → 有区别的；与众不同的
di〔s〕分离 + stingu 刺；刺激 + ish 使… → 把不同的刺分离 → 区别
distinguish 区别；辨出 + ed 表形容词 → 与众不同的 → 著名的
ex 出 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 → 拔出刺 → 灭绝的，注意：ex后接s开头的词根时省略s
extinct 灭绝的 + ion 表名词 → 灭绝
ex 出 + tingu 刺 + ish 使… → 把刺拔出，刺引申为火焰 → 熄灭
in 使… + stig〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 + ate 做，造成，使… → 刺激〔别人〕→ 煽动
in 向内 + stinct 刺；刺激 → 内在的刺激 → 本能
stimul 刺；刺激 + ate 做，造成，使… → 刺激，鼓励
stimul 刺；刺激 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 刺激，鼓励
sting 刺；刺激 + y …的 → 对钱的事挑刺 → 小气的
